# Diabetes UK Professional Conference 2021 - Conference Information
## **Welcome to the Diabetes UK Professional Conference 2021**
Taking place online from 19 to 30 April 2021, the conference will be bringing
back our prestigious Named Lectures, Professional Interest Groups and abstract
programme alongside a range of discipline and multidisciplinary sessions to
update and educate healthcare professionals, researchers and scientists in the
field of diabetes. Our three-track multidisciplinary programme will take place
over lunchtime and late afternoon slots to ensure DUKPC21 offers flexibility
for learning opportunities, supported by an on-demand option.
Our three-track programme will leave you with the diabetes knowledge you need
to provide the best care for your patients.
* Designed by healthcare professionals and spanning disciplines from primary to specialist care, podiatry, paediatrics and dietetics.
* Seven Named Lectures: exclusive insight into the latest research and understanding about diabetes treatment and care from some of the world’s leading specialists.
* Eleven professional interest group meetings: the latest updates for your profession for consultants and specialist trainees, DSNs, dieticians, eye specialists, midwives, primary care, paediatricians, podiatrists, practising pharmacists, psychologists, and research nurses.
* E-posters ranging from basic science, clinical science, education, to clinical care management, healthcare delivery and psychological care.
